<P>AN ADDRESS, DELIVERED IN THE ESSEX LODGE, UPON THE Fe&s;tival of St. John the Evangeli&s;t, AT THE INDUCTION OF THE OFFICERS BY BROTHER JOSEPH HILLER, PAST MASTER, AND BROTHER BENJAMIN HODGES, MASTER ELECT. DECEMBER 27, 1798.</P>
<P>BY WILLIAM BENTLEY, MEMBER OF ESSEX LODGE.</P>
<Q><P>"To receive gue&s;ts with honour, is the &s;acrament of men."</P>
<BIBL>INSTITUTES OF <GAP DESC="illegible" REASON="indecipherable" EXTENT="2 letters">NU.</BIBL></Q>
<Q><P>"If, in the in&s;tructions we give to others, we inquire not into the experience and in&s;titutions of pa&s;t ages, how can we profit mankind?"</P>
<BIBL>CHOU-KING.</BIBL></Q>
<P>PRINTED AT SALEM, BY JOSHUA CUSHING. 1799.</P>
